<TITLE>KSCSTE Fellowship Programme</TITLE>
<TEXT>
Kochi: Applications are invited for Kerala State  Council for Science, Technology and Environment Research Fellowship to motivate fellows and impart the skills needed for them to become lifelong learners and for them to develop leadership skills and work effectively. The period of fellowship shall be for a period not exceeding three years. 
 
The fellowship carries a monthly stipend of Rs 20,000/  per month for the first two years and Rs. 25,000/  per month for the third year.  Additionally there is an annual contingency grant of Rs. 20,000/  and HRA (10% of the Fellowship amount). 
 
Who can apply? 
 Candidates who have been awarded MSc/M Tech degree in any of the subjects listed above in 2016 and two previous years.   
 Candidates should be from among the 1stTen Rank /Position holders from any of the Universities in Kerala. 
 Age should not be more than 35 years as on 1st January 2017. 
 
Mode of Selection 
The fellowship is awarded to eligible candidates after an online test followed by an interview.  Online Examination is introduced this year. The online examination will be conducted in Thiruvananthapuram, Kochi and Kozhikode on 19 February 2017.  Candidates have to mark their choice of centres during the online registration process. Every attempt will be made by KSCSTE  to allot the centre chosen by the candidate.  However, if the number of applicants in a particular centre exceeds the permissible capacity, the candidates may be allotted to their second or third preferred centre.  The address of the online examination centre for a candidate will be mentioned in the admit card, which can be generated online.  
 
The request for changing the examination centre allotted after generation of admit cards will not be entertained under any circumstances.The final decision in this case will be that of KSCSTE.  The candidates are requested to carry the print out of admit cards and present them at  the online examination centre allotted to them, as indicated in the admit card.  The candidates will be ranked based on the marks obtained for the entrance examination and are shortlisted based on the cut off marks recommended by the KSCSTE Research Fellowship Committee for each of the subject area, candidates who have scored marks above the cut off will be called for an interview.  The entrance examination carries two papers, Paper I is common for all candidates and Paper II is one of 7 subject areas chosen by the candidate.The list of shortlisted candidates will be published in KSCSTE website and the shortlisted candidates will be notified via E mail for the interview to be held at KSCSTE, Pattom, Thiruvananthapuram. 
 
How to apply 
Candidates who wish to avail KSCSTE Research fellowship may submit their application online through http://kscste.kerala.gov.in/index.php/programmes initiatives/h r development in s t/kscste fellowship programme . The last date of online submission of applications is 8 February 2017 . The PDF of the application form generated at the end of the submission should be printed out, duly signed and mailed to the following address superscribing the envelope  Appplication for KSCSTE Research Fellowship 2016 17  on or before 15th February 2017.  
 To The Head 
